steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).. Whisk sambal oelek, rice vinegar, hoisin sauce, soy sauce, sesame oil, brown sugar, and garlic together in a small saucepan. Heat over low heat until warm, about 5 minutes; set aside.. Place broccoli florets in a microwave safe bowl. Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Add olive oil, salt, and pepper; toss to coat.. name: Lemon Caper Pasta
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'rotini pasta, or any pasta'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chicken bouillon paste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lemon, juiced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'capers'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Fill a large pot with lightly salted water and bring to a rolling boil. Stir in pasta and return to a boil. Cook pasta uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, 8 to 10 minutes. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta water. Drain pasta and set aside.. Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a skillet over medium heat. Add garlic; fry until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add remaining butter and melt, then sprinkle in flour. Whisk to combine; cook for about 1  minute.. Whisk chicken soup base into reserved pasta water; pour into skillet. Whisk to make a smooth sauce. Whisk in lemon juice, 1 tablespoon at a time, to taste. Stir in parsley and capers. Season with salt and pepper. Allow to simmer until sauce thickens, about 2 minutes.. Toss sauce with drained pasta.

name: Creamy Garlic Butter Chicken Bites

steps: Whisk salt, garlic granules, onion granules, and paprika together in a small bowl. Toss chicken in a bowl with 1 teaspoon oil and seasoning mixture; set aside.. Move chicken to the back side of the skillet. Add remaining 2 tablespoons butter. Add minced garlic, and saute until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Stir in cream. Move chicken back to center of skillet; stir into sauce to coat.

Meanwhile, whisk marmalade, BBQ sauce, and soy sauce together in a small saucepan and heat over low heat until hot, about 5 minutes.. Place nuggets in a large bowl. Drizzle sauce over the top. Toss to coat.

name: Ground Turkey Teriyaki Stir-Fry
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mirin'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sake'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'fresh ginger'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground turkey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'stir fry vegetables'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked jasmine rice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'toasted sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onion'}
steps: Stir soy sauce, mirin, sake, garlic, ginger, brown sugar, and cornstarch together in a small bowl; set aside.. Place a skillet over medium high heat. Add oil. Add ground turkey. Allow turkey to brown for 3 to 5 minutes before starting to crumble and break up with a spatula. Add in onions and stir fry vegetables. Cover and cook for 3 minutes.. Uncover and add the teriyaki sauce. Cook and stir until sauce thickens, about 3 minutes. Spoon over rice. Sprinkle sesame seeds and chopped green onions on top.

name: Spicy Vegetable Beef Udon Noodles
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dark soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili oil'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'oyster sauce'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'udon noodles'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'grapeseed oil'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'stir-fry vegetables'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'rib eye steak,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions'}
steps: Stir soy sauce, dark soy sauce, chili oil, oyster sauce, honey, sesame oil, water, and sesame seeds together in a small bowl; set aside.. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over high heat. Cook udon until tender with a bite, 8 to 10 minutes. Drain, rinse with cold water, and drain again. Set aside.. Heat grapeseed oil in the pot over medium-low heat. Add garlic and stir-fry vegetables; cook and stir for 2 minutes. Stir in beef and cook until completely browned, about 3 minutes. Add noodles back to the pan, stir in sauce, and toss until everything is evenly coated.. Season with salt and pepper. Garnish with green onions and serve.

name: 7 Cheap and Easy Dinner Ideas for Every Night of the Week
Pie Crust Cookies
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'pie crust'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'all purpose flour for dusting'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'whole milk'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'granulated sugar'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter, melted and cooled'}
steps: Gather all ingredients. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Line 2 large rimmed baking sheets with parchment paper; set aside.. Roll premade pie crust to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured work surface, and cut using desired cookie cutter shapes.. Transfer cut-outs to prepared baking sheets, leaving about a 1/2-inch space between each cookie. Repeat with remaining dough, rerolling scraps once.. Whisk together egg and milk in a small bowl until combined. Using a pastry brush, brush the tops of each cookie evenly with egg mixture; discard remaining egg mixture. Whisk together sugar, cinnamon, and salt in a small bowl until evenly combined, sprinkle evenly over brushed cookies.. Bake cookies, one baking sheet at a time, in the preheated oven until the edges and bottoms of cookies just become golden brown, about 15 minutes.. Remove from oven and brush tops of each cookie lightly with melted butter, let cool slightly on baking sheet, about 5 minutes. Serve warm.

name: Homemade Spaghetti-O's
ingredients: {'quantity': '16', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'ring-shaped pasta \xa0(Anelli Siciliani)'}, {'quantity': '30', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'tomato sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Cantanzaro herbs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'meatballs'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shaved Parmesan cheese,'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh basil,'}
steps: Fill a large pot with lightly salted water and bring to a rolling boil. Stir in pasta and return to a boil. Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 8 minutes. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta water, drain pasta, and set aside.. Add tomato sauce, Cantanzaro herbs, sugar, salt. and pepper to the pot; bring to a simmer over medium-low heat.. Meanwhile, cut each meatball into 4 pieces. Roll each piece into a mini meatball. Garnish with basil leaves and Parmesan shavings and serve immediately.

name: Spicy Garlic Udon Noodles
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'hoisin sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(8 ounce) blocks', 'name': 'udon noodles'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'green onions'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'toasted sesame seeds'}
steps: Prepare the sauce by combining garlic, soy sauce, hoisin, sesame oil, and red pepper flakes in a small bowl; set aside.. Bring a large pot of water to a boil, and add udon blocks. Let them sit in the water until they start to unwind, 1 to 2 minutes. Noodles should remain a little chewy. Drain noodles, and return to the pot.. Add sauce, and stir until noodles are well coated. Move to a serving dish, garnish with sliced green onions and sesame seeds, and serve.

name: Crustless Grilled Cheese
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'white sandwich bread'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, or as needed'}
steps: Spread a thin layer of butter onto 1 side of each slice of bread.. Using a round cookie cutter that is slightly smaller than the sandwich sealer, press out round slices of cheese. Lay 4 slices of bread on a work surface, buttered side down. Place a cheese round in the center of each slice. Top with remaining 4 bread slices, buttered side up.. Center a sandwich sealer over a sandwich, press the sealer down, and hold it in place to seal the edges, 15 to 30 seconds. Pull the crusts away from the sealer; discard. Repeat with remaining sandwiches.. Place sandwich discs on a parchment-lined baking sheet and freeze for 2 hours before transferring into a freezer bag.. Preheat the air fryer to 380 degrees F (193 degrees C). Cook frozen sandwiches until golden, about 5 minutes. If sandwiches are thawed, cook 3 minutes at 370 degrees F (188 degrees C).

name: S’Mores in a Bag

steps: Open snack bags and add chocolate candy pieces.. Roast 3 marshmallows over a campfire or grill according to desired degree of doneness; add marshmallows to bag. Allow the warmth of the marshmallows to melt the chocolate, mix cookie-marshmallow mixture around slightly, and serve immediately.

name: 3-Ingredient Baked Goat Cheese Dip
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce)', 'name': 'goat cheese log'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'marinara sauce'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher or sea salt (optional)'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh basil, cut into ribbons'}

Gently spoon marinara sauce around the border, taking care to cover the edge of goat cheese but not the middle. Sprinkle with salt.. Bake in the preheated oven until goat cheese is hot and soft and marinara sauce is hot and bubbling, 20 to 25 minutes.. Remove from the oven and sprinkle with freshly chopped basil.

name: Broccoli Alfredo Pasta
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'farfalle pasta'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'broccoli florets'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese (see Note)'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'ground nutmeg, or to taste'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh parsley sprigs for garnish (optional)'}
steps: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook farfalle pasta at a boil, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 12 minutes. Remove to a colander; reserve the pasta water for later use.. Add broccoli to a microwave-safe container along with 1/4 cup water. Stir in cream and allow to simmer, stirring often, 3 to 4 minutes.. Add cheese and garlic, stirring continuously, until cheese is melted. Stir in nutmeg and remove from heat. sauce is too thick, stir in a bit of reserved pasta water. Season to taste with salt and pepper.. To serve, combine cooked pasta, cooked broccoli, and sauce. Garnish with fresh parsley sprigs, if desired.

name: Asparagus and Eggs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic clove'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': None, 'name': 'asparagus stalks, trimmed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'red pepper flakes (optional)'}
steps: Heat a small skillet over medium-high heat. Add olive oil and garlic; cook and stir until garlic is fragrant, about 30 seconds.. Add asparagus and cook until fork-tender, turning asparagus often to ensure even cooking, about 4 minutes.. Spread asparagus out and crack 2 eggs over the asparagus. Cover with lid and cook until egg whites are firm and yolk is done to desired consistency, about 4 minutes.. Season with salt and pepper; sprinkle with red pepper flakes and serve immediately.

name: Homemade Hamburger Helper
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'lean ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'yellow onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ketchup'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '3 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'beef broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'elbow macaroni'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'Cheddar cheese,'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Heat a large, heavy-bottomed pot over medium-high heat. Add beef and onion, and cook, stirring occasionally, until beef is crumbled, browned, and no longer pink, about 7 minutes. Spoon off and discard any fat.. Stir in tomato paste, ketchup, garlic powder, chili powder, salt, paprika, and pepper; cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, about 2 minutes.. Add beef broth, and bring to a boil over high heat. Stir in macaroni; reduce heat to medium, and gently boil, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until pasta is tender and most of the liquid is absorbed, 13 to 15 minutes.. Remove from heat, and stir in Cheddar, ensuring cheese is fully melted and incorporated, 30 to 45 seconds. Let stand until thickened before serving, about 2 minutes.

name: Easy Sheet Pan Roasted Greek Salmon and Broccoli
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'broccoli'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '6-ounce)', 'name': 'salmon filets'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lemon,'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'feta cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Add broccoli to the prepared baking sheet, drizzle with olive oil, and sprinkle with salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Toss to coat and spread in an even layer on the baking sheet. Create 4 spaces within the broccoli for salmon filets and place each filet in an empty space.. Combine Dijon, honey, and balsamic vinegar in a small bowl and stir well. Spread mustard mixture over each salmon piece and sprinkle each piece evenly with Greek seasoning.. Bake in the preheated oven until fish flakes easily with a fork, about 12 minutes, or until desired doneness. Remove from the oven; squeeze lemon juice over the sheet pan and top with crumbled feta.

name: One Pot Spinach Mushroom Pasta
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'yellow onion,'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'white mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red chile flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'rotini pasta'}, {'quantity': '1 (5', 'unit': 'ounce) bag', 'name': 'baby spinach'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}
steps: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and mushrooms. Cook for 7 minutes. Add garlic and crushed chile flakes. Cook for 1 minute.. Stir in salt, broth, and pasta. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, and cook at a simmer for 10 minutes, stirring halfway through.. Turn off heat. Add spinach, cover, and let sit for 2 minutes. Stir in Parmesan and lemon juice. Serve immediately.

name: 25 Recipes to Make With Brownie Mix (That Taste Like They're From-Scratch)
Easy Lemon Cheesecake Crème Brulée "Donuts"
ingredients: {'quantity': '12', 'unit': None, 'name': 'Hawaiian rolls'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cheesecake filling'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'lemon curd'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lemon, zested'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}
steps: Gather the ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a 9x13-inch baking dish or rimmed baking sheet with parchment.. Brush each roll with melted butter and place in the prepared pan. Bake in the preheated oven until lightly toasted, about 5 minutes.. Combine cheesecake filling, lemon curd, and 1 teaspoon lemon zest in a bowl and stir well.. Add mixture to a piping bag or large resealable plastic bag. Make a small cut in one corner of the bag.. Use a paring knife to make a small cut into the side of each roll, creating an opening large enough to pipe the filling into without going all the way through. Fill each roll with about 1 1/2 tablespoons filling and return to the baking dish.. Add sugar and water to a small saucepan; bring to a simmer over medium-high heat. Reduce heat to medium-low and cook, without stirring, until lightly golden brown, about 10 minutes; remove from heat.. Line a rimmed baking sheet with parchment, and set a rack over the sheet. Working very carefully, dip the top of each roll into sugar mixture and place it right side up on the rack.. Grate remaining lemon zest over rolls. Let stand until completely cooled and lightly hardened on top, 10 to 15 minutes. If sugar mixture becomes too thick before all rolls are coated, return the pot to low heat and swirl it lightly until it melts again.

name: Chicken and Waffles Casserole

steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease a 9x13-inch baking dish. Arrange waffles on a baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until lightly toasted on each side, about 4 minutes per side. Remove; cut each waffle into 8 pieces. and arrange waffles in the prepared baking dish.. Cut larger chicken nuggets in half, leaving smaller pieces whole, and arrange chicken pieces among the waffles.. Whisk together eggs, half-and-half, 2 tablespoons maple syrup, salt, and cayenne pepper in a large bowl until well combined and slightly frothy. Pour egg mixture over waffles and chicken; cover and let stand 15 minutes to soak before baking.. Bake until eggs are set and top is golden brown, about 1 hour, uncovering halfway through baking time. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Drizzle with melted butter and syrup.

name: Pan-Seared Cod with Lemon Aioli
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon zest'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon juice, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'milk, or more as needed'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(6 ounce)', 'name': 'cod filets'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}
steps: For lemon aioli: Stir mayonnaise, lemon zest, lemon juice, and grated garlic together in a small bowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Thin to a drizzling consistency with milk.. For fish: Pat fish dry with a paper towel. Heat olive oil and butter in a skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle both sides of cod with Italian seasoning, salt, and pepper.. Add cod to the hot skillet and sear until golden brown on both sides and fish flakes easily with a fork, 3 to 4 minutes per side. Transfer to serving plates, and serve with lemon aioli.

name: Savory Puff Pastry Twists with Parmesan and Everything Seasoning
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': '17.3 ounce', 'name': 'puff pastry sheets (1 sheet)'}, {'quantity': '1 1/3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'everything bagel sesame seasoning blend'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ketchup'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Dijon mustard, or as needed for dipping (optional)'}
steps: Thaw puff pastry at room temperature until just pliable, about 1 hour, or according to package directions.. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a 12x18-inch sheet pan with parchment paper.. Sprinkle the parchment paper with 1/2 the cheese and 1/2 the seasoning blend, in an area about the same size as the puff pastry sheet.. Brush one side of pastry with beaten egg, and lay pastry in the prepared pan, egg-wash-side down.. Lightly flour a rolling pin, allowing any excess to fall on pastry. Roll pastry to press seasoning and cheese into the bottom of pastry sheet.. With a sharp knife or bench scraper, cut pastry lengthwise into 9 strips, and then cut strips in half crosswise, to make a total of 18 strips.. Brush tops of pastry strips with egg wash, then sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and seasoning blend. Lift the ends of each strip and gently twist; arrange twists on the pan, leaving space between them.. Bake in the center of the preheated oven until browned, about 10 minutes. Remove the pan from the oven, and use tongs to turn each twist over; bake 5 minutes more.. Remove from the oven to cool slightly on a rack. Serve warm, as bread sticks with a meal, or as appetizers, with ketchup and Dijon mustard for dipping.
